raw.subject: Defines the A-profile Arm CPU architecture including the A32 (ARM), T32 (Thumb), and A64 instruction sets. The A (Application) profile defines a Virtual Memory System Architecture (VMSA) with support for the AArch64 and AArch32 Execution states, Virtualization and TrustZone Security. Includes the Debug Architecture, the GIC CPU interface, and the Generic Timer, Performance Monitors Extensions, and Activity Monitors Extensions.
